# ibinet-sdk Context

- This package is the shared source of truth for cross-app models, helpers, middleware, and services.
- Keep framework-agnostic package quality; avoid app-specific business logic unless it is intentionally shared.
- Do not add migrations here; shared schema is maintained mainly by IDC.
- Preserve helper APIs (`has()`, `setting()`, route helpers) and Blade directives because many apps depend on them.
- Maintain compatibility for critical services like `ApprovalService` and `TechnicianBorrowService`.
- Prefer extending existing `Ibinet\Models\*` conventions (UUIDs, SoftDeletes, activity logging patterns).

## Import Convention (Strict)

All consuming apps MUST use PHP `use` statements at the top of files. **Never call SDK classes, models, or helpers via direct FQCN inline strings** (e.g. `\Ibinet\Helpers\UserHelper::getUserProjectByRoles(...)`).

Correct:
```php
use Ibinet\Helpers\UserHelper;
use Ibinet\Helpers\ConditionalHelper;

UserHelper::getUserProjectByRoles($id, ['IBOS']);
ConditionalHelper::canAssignTechnician($userId, $projectId);
```

Incorrect (forbidden):
```php
\Ibinet\Helpers\UserHelper::getUserProjectByRoles(...);   // ❌ FQCN inline
\Ibinet\Models\User::find(...);                           // ❌ FQCN inline
```

This rule applies to ALL files in all consuming apps (idc, ier, omc, ifos, ibinet-sso).
